name: Peach Coffee Cake II
author: Cookin_Queen
summary: This is a great recipe I came up with when our white peach tree yielded sooo many peaches I had to figure out many ways to use them.... Even my kids love this one -- they will eat it all day....
ingredients: 4 cups peeled, pitted and sliced peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C)
Grease and flour a 9x13 inch baking pan
In a large bowl, cream together 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup butter
Beat in sour cream, vanilla, and eggs
Mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt
Spread 1/2 the batter into the baking pan
Layer with peaches, and top with remaining batter
In a small bowl, mix 1/4 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar, pecans, and cinnamon
Cut in cold butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs
Bake 45 minutes in the preheated oven, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean
